parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The detachment of the rear spoiler can cause accidents or near-misses, as it can fall off and strike other vehicles or pedestrians, potentially leading to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The rear spoiler suddenly detaches from the vehicle while driving
often with a loud noise or vibration
and may strike other vehicles or pedestrians.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door latch can cause the door to open unexpectedly while driving, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The door appears to be latched but opens unexpectedly while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fracture of the weather strip can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially lead to a burning plastic odor.
symptoms: The weather strip fractures
causing a burning plastic odor.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Failure (Fuel Outlet Flange Cracking)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the fuel outlet flange mounted on the fuel tank can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, or other safety risks.
symptoms: Fuel odor inside or outside the vehicle
fuel leaking from underneath the vehicle
strong odor of gasoline present inside the cabin of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for recall repairs can delay necessary fixes, leaving vehicles in an unsafe condition and putting drivers at risk.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but parts are not available
dealers confirm parts are not yet available
manufacturer exceeds reasonable time for recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks and strong fuel odors can lead to accidents, fires, and explosions, posing a significant risk to vehicle occupants and other road users.
symptoms: Strong smell of gasoline inside and outside the vehicle
fuel leaking from the fuel tank or fuel pump
fuel pouring out of the bottom of the vehicle
restricted performance warning on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked or fractured fuel pump flange can cause fuel leaks, leading to accidents, fires, and explosions.
symptoms: Fuel leaking from the fuel pump flange
strong smell of gasoline
fuel squirting out of the fuel filter/pump.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An inaccurate fuel gauge can lead to unexpected fuel depletion, causing vehicles to stall or run out of fuel on the highway, which can be dangerous.
symptoms: Fuel gauge not working properly
vehicle running out of gas despite showing a quarter tank of gas left.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to replace Takata airbags in a timely manner can lead to spontaneous deployment, causing injuries and accidents, and also affects the trade-in value of the vehicle.
symptoms: Delayed or unavailable repair parts
refusal to replace airbags due to location
spontaneous deployment of side curtain airbags
fragments of metal and plastic sent into the interior of the car.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall repair parts can lead to delayed repairs, leaving vehicles in an unsafe condition, and affecting the trade-in value of the vehicle.
symptoms: Delayed or unavailable repair parts
manufacturer exceeding a reasonable amount of time for recall repair
parts on backorder
inability to trade-in the car.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Spontaneous airbag deployment can cause injuries and accidents, and also affect the safety and performance of the vehicle.
symptoms: Side curtain airbags deployed spontaneously
fragments of metal and plastic sent into the interior of the car
vehicle was driving at a low speed on a neighborhood street.
